"   <div id=\"basicsTopicLeft\">",
"    <div id=\"topicTitle\">",
"     Patient information: Fungal nail infections (The Basics)",
"    </div>",
"    <span class=\"view\">",
"     View in",
"     <a class=\"lang\" href=\"./es-419/fungal-nail-infections-the-basics?source=topic_page\">",
"      Spanish",
"     </a>",
"    </span>",
"    <a class=\"contributor contributor_credentials\" href=\"./authors-and-editors/patient-information\">",
"     Written by the doctors and editors at UpToDate",
"    </a>",
"    <div id=\"topicText\">",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H20278040\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What is a fungal nail infection?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;A fungal nail infection is an infection of the nail that makes it get thick or turn white, yellow, or brown. It is caused by a type of germ called a &ldquo;fungus.&rdquo;",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Fungal infections happen in the toenails more often than the fingernails. They usually start on the big toe, and can affect 1 or more nails. People who have a toenail infection might also have a condition known as &ldquo;athlete&rsquo;s foot&rdquo; (a fungal infection of the foot). That&rsquo;s because certain types of fungi (plural of fungus) can cause both of these problems.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Fungi like to grow in warm and wet places. People who swim or whose feet sweat a lot might have a higher chance of getting a fungal nail infection.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H20278055\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What are the symptoms of a fungal nail infection?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;A fungal infection can cause a nail to:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Turn white, yellow or brown (",
"        <a class=\"graphic graphic_picture graphicRef66584 \" href=\"mobipreview.htm?7/33/7699\">",
"         picture 1",
"        </a>",
"        )",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Get thick, change shape, or lift up",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Break off easily",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Hurt",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Fungal nail infections don&rsquo;t usually lead to serious long-term problems. But in some people they can. In people who have diabetes or whose bodies have trouble fighting infections, the infection can spread to other parts of the body.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H20278070\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Is there a test for a fungal nail infection?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. Usually, your doctor or nurse can tell if you have a fungal nail infection by talking with you and doing an exam. But to make sure, he or she might take a small sample of the nail and look at it under a microscope. Your doctor might also send the sample to a lab where another doctor can see which germs are causing the infection.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H20278085\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Can I treat my fungal nail infection on my own?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;You can buy over-the-counter creams or products, but they usually don&rsquo;t work.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H20278100\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How are fungal nail infections treated?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Treatment depends, in part, on how severe the infection is, and how much it bothers you. If your infection is mild or doesn&rsquo;t bother you very much, you might choose not to treat it. An untreated nail infection probably won&rsquo;t go away, but it probably won&rsquo;t cause any long-term problems either.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      When people need or choose to have treatment, it usually involves &ldquo;antifungal&rdquo; medicines. These medicines are taken by mouth, and treatment usually lasts a few months. Some people who take these medicines need to have blood tests. That&rsquo;s because these medicines can affect the liver.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      If you don&rsquo;t want to or can&rsquo;t take antifungal medicines, your doctor will talk with you about other treatment options. These might include using an antifungal nail polish or having surgery to remove your nail.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Before starting any of these treatments, you should know that:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        It can take many months for your nail to look normal again. &nbsp;",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        There is a chance that the treatment won&rsquo;t work. The infection might not get better, or it might come back. If either of these things happen, your doctor can try another treatment or send you to a specialist.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H20278115\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Can fungal nail infections be prevented?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Sometimes. To reduce your chance of getting one, you can:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Keep your feet clean and dry.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Avoid sharing nail tools, such as clippers and scissors.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Wear flip-flops or other footwear in a gym shower or locker room.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H20278130\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What if I want to get pregnant?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;If you want to get pregnant, let your doctor or nurse know. He or she might recommend that you not take certain antifungal medicines during pregnancy.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H20278145\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       More on this topic",
"      </span>",
"     </p>",
